HEADWORD: Disallowance
<hw>Dis`al*low"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
disallowing; refusal to admit or permit; rejection.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Disapprobation; prohibition; condemnation;
censure; rejection.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

